headline: Chinese Coffee Chain Wants To De-Throne Starbucks, But Experts Say Its Business Model Will Never Work
summary: Luckin Coffee surpassed Starbucks (NASDAQ:SBUX) as the largest coffee chain in China in 2023. Now, it's setting its sights on the U.S. Luckin opened its first U.S. store in New York City's East Village neighborhood earlier this spring. As of this month, the company has five locations across the city. headline: Plant-Based Dairy Products Market to Reach USD 34 Billion by 2030 | Insights on Milk, Cheese, Yogurt, and Emerging Alternatives: MarkNtel Advisors
summary: The Global Plant-Based Dairy Products Market is experiencing strong momentum, driven by changing consumer behavior and rising awareness of health and sustainability. Valued at USD 20 billion in 2024, the market is projected to reach USD 34 billion by 2030, expanding at a CAGR of 9% during 2025–2030.
